<div id="review_1538588448" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1538588448" />
    <a title="Judy Gill" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/13889790-judy-gill"><img alt="Judy Gill" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1442473408p2/13889790.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1538588448?book_show_action=true">Feb 05, 2016</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Judy Gill" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Judy Gill" href="/user/show/13889790-judy-gill">Judy Gill</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was ok"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was ok</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/27830286-waterkill">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1538588448" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer16715399888004244559"><strong>Not all bad</strong><br/><br/>Disclaimer: I was offered a free copy of this book in exchange for an unbiased review. I declined the offer and purchased a copy.<br/>WATERKILL, by Mark Donavan, while fairly well plotted, with a well-motivated villain, suffers badly from a lack of editing, and too great a reliance on a spell-checking program. WATERKILL could have risen above the two stars awarded here if the author had made the effort to employ an editor, or at the very least, a proofreader with the education and intellig</span>
  <span id="freeText16715399888004244559" style="display:none"><strong>Not all bad</strong><br /><br />Disclaimer: I was offered a free copy of this book in exchange for an unbiased review. I declined the offer and purchased a copy.<br />WATERKILL, by Mark Donavan, while fairly well plotted, with a well-motivated villain, suffers badly from a lack of editing, and too great a reliance on a spell-checking program. WATERKILL could have risen above the two stars awarded here if the author had made the effort to employ an editor, or at the very least, a proofreader with the education and intelligence to spot basic, beginner errors. The stilted dialogue, often used to "instruct" the reader, would have been less so had the author used a more terse style with more contractions, especially in tense situations, of which there were many. I like thrillers, but doubt I'll buy another in this series. </span>
  <a data-text-id="16715399888004244559" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


